									<h5 id="subject_1512">
										<a href="http://www.bitcointrading.com/forum/linux-distros/bamt-version-0-5-easy-usb-based-mining-linux-with-farm-wide-management-tools/msg1512/?PHPSESSID=hp70s9d1hbdcpafag006e54sr6#msg1512" rel="nofollow">Re: BAMT version 0.5 - Update BAMT with the latest cgminer</a>
									</h5>
									<div class="smalltext">&#171; <strong>Reply #3 on:</strong> June 18, 2012, 12:39:02 pm &#187;</div>
									<div id="msg_1512_quick_mod"></div>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="post">
								<div class="inner" id="msg_1512"><span id="post_updatingcgminer">Bitcointalk</span> member tosku has a quick guide on how to update BAMT with the latest version of cgminer, here are his instructions:<br /><br /><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote">Quote from: tosku <a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=65915.msg972078#msg972078" class="bbc_link" target="_blank">https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=65915.msg972078#msg972078</a></div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote"><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">I updated BAMT with the latest version of cgminer. This is how I did it. I&#039;m sure there are more elegant or &quot;correct&quot; ways, but this worked for me. If I&#039;m doing something horribly wrong, please point it out.<br /><br />Logged in as root, type this into a terminal to download the latest cgminer and prepare it with the ADL SDK:</span><br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code: <a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return smfSelectText(this);" class="codeoperation">[Select]</a></div><code class="bbc_code">cd /usr/share<br />git clone https://github.com/ckolivas/cgminer.git<br />cd cgminer/ADL_SDK<br />wget http://download2-developer.amd.com/amd/GPU/zip/ADL_SDK_4.0.zip<br />unzip ADL_SDK_4.0.zip<br />cd include<br />mv adl* ..<br />cd ..<br />cd ..</code><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">Keep going. The following instructions on compiling cgminer are taken from <a href="http://ck.kolivas.org/apps/cgminer/README" class="bbc_link" target="_blank">http://ck.kolivas.org/apps/cgminer/README</a></span><br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code: <a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return smfSelectText(this);" class="codeoperation">[Select]</a></div><code class="bbc_code">cd /opt<br />tar xf /opt/AMD-APP-SDK-v2.4-lnx32/icd-registration.tgz<br />ln -s /opt/AMD-APP-SDK-v2.4-lnx32/include/CL /usr/include<br />ln -s /opt/AMD-APP-SDK-v2.4-lnx32/lib/x86/* /usr/lib/<br />ldconfig<br /><br />cd /usr/share/cgminer<br />./autogen.sh<br />CFLAGS=&quot;-O2 -Wall -march=native&quot; ./configure<br />make</code><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">Now that cgminer is compiled, you need to replace the cgminer that came with BAMT with the latest version. It&#039;s a good idea to stop mining before doing that, and to make a backup of the old cgminer:</span><br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code: <a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return smfSelectText(this);" class="codeoperation">[Select]</a></div><code class="bbc_code">gpumon<br />D<br />q<br />cd /opt/miners<br />mkdir cgminer_backup<br />cd cgminer<br />cp * ../cgminer_backup/<br /><br />cd /usr/share/cgminer<br />cp * /opt/miners/cgminer</code><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">Now restart mining and verify that things work as they should:</span><br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code: <a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return smfSelectText(this);" class="codeoperation">[Select]</a></div><code class="bbc_code">gpumon<br />S<br />0</code><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">You should see the latest version of cgminer running in a screen.</span></blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div></div>
							</div>
						</div>
