							<div class="post">
								<div class="inner" id="msg_1681"><span id="post_readonlyfilesystem">Someone</span> has found a solution to the &#039;read-only file system&#039; problem, I&#039;ve had it a few times, it&#039;s really annoying.<br /><br /><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote">Quote from: Transisto <a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=65915.msg1005065#msg1005065" class="bbc_link" target="_blank">https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=65915.msg1005065#msg1005065</a></div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote"><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">Read-only file system problem.</span><br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code: <a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return smfSelectText(this);" class="codeoperation">[Select]</a></div><code class="bbc_code">rm: cannot remove `/live/image/BAMT/CONTROL/ACTIVE/noOCGPU3&#039;: Read-only file system</code><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size">Did a Scandisk under windows,</span><br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code: <a href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return smfSelectText(this);" class="codeoperation">[Select]</a></div><code class="bbc_code">151k recovered in 9 file,&nbsp; &nbsp;autocong cgsnoop phoenix2, and CHECK_NETWORK.SH , entry trunkated</code><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>Problem fixed.</strong></span></blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div><br />My solution to that problem is to keep reformatting the stick.&nbsp; Problem comes up, I reformat, good to go...&nbsp; But this might be a quicker way to get mining again!</div>
