								<div class="inner" id="msg_4524"><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote"><a href="http://www.bitcointrading.com/forum/linux-distros/bamt-version-0-5-easy-usb-based-mining-linux-with-farm-wide-management-tools/msg4523/?PHPSESSID=hp70s9d1hbdcpafag006e54sr6#msg4523">Quote from: tonyadams on April 12, 2013, 06:18:09 am</a></div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote">Hello, <br />I have this problem bamt v 0.4 boots normal but 0.5c :<br />SYSLINUX 4.02 debia-20101014CHS Copyright (C) 1994-2010 H. Peter Anvin et al<br />ERROR: No configuration file found<br />No DEFAULT or UI configuration directive found!<br />boot:<br /><br /><br />I read around and looks like this will fix the problem :<br /><br />&quot; i looked through the image.&nbsp; the original &quot;0.4&quot; image used a fat16 partition, but the 0.5 uses a fat32.&nbsp; this was due to a request from someone who thought it would help their motherboard boot.&nbsp; as far as i know, it didn&#039;t make any difference.<br /><br />maybe some motherboards can&#039;t deal with fat32?&nbsp; i don&#039;t know, but it is the only difference I can find between the two.&nbsp; i&#039;ll upload an image using fat16 later if someone wants to try it.&quot;<br /><br />&quot;&nbsp; fat16 image works and boots as expected &quot;<br /><br />&nbsp;The website this image was uploaded to, is not working anymore. Any chance some one have a working link to 0.5c image with fat16 file system? Please help.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div>What kind of motherboard do you have?</div>
